Package com.apptasticsoftware.rssreader.internal.stream

Class AutoCloseStream<T>

java.lang.Object
com.apptasticsoftware.rssreader.internal.stream.AbstractAutoCloseStream<T,Stream<T>>
com.apptasticsoftware.rssreader.internal.stream.AutoCloseStream<T>
All Implemented Interfaces:
AutoCloseable, BaseStream<T,Stream<T>>, Stream<T>
public class AutoCloseStream<T> extends AbstractAutoCloseStream<T,Stream<T>> implements Stream<T>
A Stream that automatically calls its AbstractAutoCloseStream.close() method after a terminating operation, such as limit(), forEach(), or collect(), has been executed.

This class is useful for working with streams that have resources that need to be closed, such as file streams or network connections.

If the AbstractAutoCloseStream.close() method is called manually, the stream will be closed and any subsequent operations will throw an IllegalStateException.

The iterator() and spliterator() methods are not supported by this class.
